default(2) and (3) of the clause amend
default the 1980 Act to allow the Secretary of State to prescribe in regulations certain kinds of land in England in respect of which applications for public path extinguishment or diversion orders may be made. 
defaultThe department
default considers this is important, but not so important as
default to require a higher degree of p
defaultarliamentary scrutiny than that offered by the negative resolution procedure. 
defaultThe department 
defaulttherefore considers the negative resolution procedure to be appropriate and proportionate.
