default Highways Act
default 1980 so as to limit the application of the charging provisions within those sections to Wales. The effect of this is to allow the Secretary of State (in relation to England) to use the power under section 150 of the 1989 Act to authorise charges to be imposed in respect of applications under sections 118ZA and 119ZA. 
default&#xa0;
