default 
defaultto (4) expands the existing regulation-making powers in sections 49 and 51. The department continues to consider that the power to make provision by regulation for the examination of vehicles submitted for roadworthiness testing should be delegated to the Secretary of State. The detail of such provisions is more appropriate to secondary legislation. There is also likely to be a need to amend such provisions and make further provision from time to time which would be less conveniently achieved if contained in primary legislation.  
