default&#xa0;
defaultIntroduction
default227.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThis clause provides the Secretary of State with an additional method for changing the model clauses for petroleum licences.
default&#xa0;
default228.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSection 2 of the Petroleum Act 1998 (a Consolidation Act) provides that Her Majesty has the exclusive right of searching for and boring and getting petroleum which exists in its natural condition in strata in Great Britain. Her Majesty has similar rights in respect of petroleum in areas of the UK which are outside territorial waters, by virtue of section 1(1) of the Continental Shelf Act 1964. Section 3 of the 1998 Act authorises the Secretary of State, acting on behalf of Her Majesty, to grant licences to others to bore for and get the petroleum referred to in both Acts. 
default&#xa0;
default229.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSection 4 of the 1998 Act places a duty on the Secretary of State to make regulations concerning various aspects of petroleum licences, such as the content and procedure for licence applications, licence fees, the areas in respect of which applications can be made and model clauses to be incorporated in licences. Regulations made under section 4 are subject to the negative resolution procedure.
default&#xa0;
default230.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe model clauses set out in regulations must be included in licences unless the Secretary of State thinks that they should be modified or excluded in any particular case. The model clauses have been amended over time, and so petroleum licences issued at different times contain different clauses. The model clauses for all licences granted before 5th March 2004 can be found in consolidated form in the Petroleum (Current Model Clauses) 
defaultOrder
default 1999 (S.I. 1999/160) and in  the Petroleum (Production) (Landward Areas) Regulations 1995 (S.I. 1995/1436). The model clauses for more recently issued licences are contained in, or determined by reference to, regulations made in S.I. 2004/352, 2006/784, 2008/225, 2009/2814 and 2009/3283.
