default343.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe purpose of clause 62 is to enable the Secretary of State to use delegated legislation to make such provision as is appropriate in consequence of the Act. Such provision may include transitional, transitory or saving provision, and amendments, repeals, revocations or other modifications of any provision of primary or subordinate legislation. 
default&#xa0;
default344.
